Information on Personal Data Protection Policy
ESTECO collects and uses personal data both off and online for communication, service supply and administration management.
In compliance with the section 13 of Italian Law n. 196/2003 and the EU Regulation 2016//679 on GDPR, this page provides information on
data collection, management and storage, cancellation timelines and users’ rights
based on the purpose of processing users’ data.
ESTECO SpA, legal address in Padriciano 99, 34149 Trieste (TS), Italy, is the controller of the management of this data. At any time the user can contact the controller for any matter related to personal data protection and its management by emailing
dataprotection@esteco.com
o by calling +39 040 3755548.
Data collection methods
We collect personal, not sensitive, data provided to ESTECO by the user for different purposes. This includes contact and information related to professional and academic background and experience, and country of residence. Additionally we store administrative data related to purchases and participation to off and online events run by ESTECO.
Data is collected online (e.g. via webforms, registration to the website and events, purchase orders, emails) or offline (e.g. contact details taken at conferences and events in general).
Cookies
This information relates to personal data given voluntarily and explicitly by the user which is stored by ESTECO SpA. ‘Cookies’ are browsing data memorized in the user’s browser while visiting our website to improve their experience and collect statistical information. Visit our
Cookie Policy
page to understand how we use cookies.
Personal data use
The acquired data is managed both manually and electronically and is stored in paper and digital archives that are complying with security standards under the existing law. Only the person(s) in charge of the processing of personal data within ESTECO SpA can handle users’ personal data.
Legal Bases
Some of the purposes of processing personal data require a specific and explicit consent that can be revoked by the user (see below). In other cases the consent is implicit since personal data management becomes necessary for the service provided. Specific processing purposes are described below, with respective legal basis for data processing.
Third Parties
For some other purposes of processing listed below, data could be shared with Third Parties. ESTECO SpA works globally through agents with different agreements and territorial jurisdictions. In order to comply with some requests ESTECO SpA needs to share the data with the local agent/distributor, who becomes the ‘Data Processor’ (although some agents are Co-Data Controllers).
1. Administrative purposes
Clients’ and prospects’ data are collected and stored for administrative purposes. Personal information is saved in internal and external databases and can be accessed only by sales and administration members of staff. This data acquisition and its storage is necessary for administrative purposes and to provide the client with product updates and support. This data can be shared with Third Parties (agents) for admin purposes linked to contractual obligations.
E.g: If you bought one of our software licences or asked for a trial, the data you provided (personal and accounting information, type of licence and its duration) is stored in our licence and sales portals. If you purchased a licence from a local agent, we will share your data with them for the same purpose.
Rights
: Users have the right to know which data we keep on file, how we store them and request cancellation or verify its cancellation within the legal deadline.
Legal basis
: legal obligation / performance of a contract. Specific consent is unsolicited, implicit
Storage Time
: 10 years
2. Service purposes
Some of the data is provided to us along with specific requests. Support requests, demo licence releases, off and online events enrolments, company website’s registrations, they all require a series of data necessary to provide the requested services. Data is saved on the company database and is used by administrative, marketing and support teams exclusively for this purpose. Data can be transferred to Third Parties (partners and distributors) working in their geographical areas of competence. Your data will never be used to send you newsletters or sales communication unless you gave us your specific consent (see purpose 3.).
Examples
If you register for an online webinar or at a conference organized by ESTECO, your data will be used for organizing purposes and to send you information and logistic communication related to the same event as well as for a final follow up. At the end of the event we won’t use your data for any other type of communication, unless you specifically signed up for it.
If you fill out a form to request a demo or for an inquiry, your data will be used to answer your query. In order to fulfill your request your data may be shared with one of our trusted partners operating in your region.
Rights
: Users have the right to know which data we keep on file, how we store them and request cancellation or verify its cancellation within the legal deadline.
Legal basis
: performance of a contract. Specific consent is unsolicited, implicit
Storage Time:
10 years
3. Information purposes/newsletter
Various forms in our website give you the chance to subscribe for a newsletter by ticking a box. Users ticking the box will receive information and communication about company and products news and events organized or supported by ESTECO. Data will be stored in our emailing system exclusively for this purpose and won’t be shared with Third Parties. The persons in charge of the processing will handle the data.
E.g.: By registering for one of our webinars, you can opt in to receive our communications. At the bottom of each email you can find a link to unsubscribe from our mailing list or to update your preferences.
Rights
: Users have the right to know their preferences stored in our emailing system and request cancellation or verify its cancellation within the legal deadline.
Legal basis
: Specific consent requested upon subscription and can be changed via the specific link provided at the bottom of the email or by emailing us at
dataprotection@esteco.com
.
Storage Time
: 10 years
4. Commercial purposes/profiling
Some forms within our website give you the chance to give your consent to receive commercial communication as:
Emails with personalized information based on your browsing preferences within our website;
Direct contact from one of our experts to give you specific answers.
This data will be stored on our website and on our marketing automation service systems. Data can be transferred to Third Parties (partners and distributors) working in their geographical areas of competence.
E.g.: By subscribing to a webinar, you can opt in giving your specific consent to receive personalized email communication. For instance, if you downloaded aerospace optimization related material from our website, we could occasionally send you updates on new materials, webinars or promotions and events related to this topic.
Rights
: Users have the right to know their preferences stored in our system and request or verify cancellation of the data within the legal deadline by emailing
dataprotection@esteco.com
.
Legal basis
: specific consent requested upon subscription and can be changed by emailing us at
dataprotection@esteco.com
.
Storage Time
: 10 years
